quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  33,9,"You who believe, remember God´s favor upon you when the armies charged at you! We sent a wind and even armies you did not see against them. God was Observant of what you were doing"
  33,10,"as they came at you both from above you and from below you, and your eyesight faltered and your hearts leaped up into your throats, and you entertained certain thoughts about God"
  33,11,there believers were tested and severely shaken as if in an earthquake
  33,12,"Thus hypocrites and those whose hearts contain malice said: \"God and His messenger have only promised us something to lure us on"
  33,13,"So when a faction of them said: \"O people of Yathrib, there is no room for you, so return!\", a group of them took leave of the Prophet, saying: \"Our houses lie exposed.\" They were not defenseless; they merely wanted to run away"
  33,14,"If a raid had been made on them from [all] its quarters, then they had been asked to rise up in dissension, they would have done so and yet not lasted very long"
  33,15,"Still they had already pledged to God that they would not turn their backs! Any oath [made] to God will be asked about"
  33,16,"SAY: \"Fleeing will never help you: if you should flee from death or slaughter, then you will still enjoy (life) only briefly"
  33,17,"SAY: \"Who is there to shield you from God if He should want any ill for you or wants mercy for you?\" They will find they have no patron nor any supporter besides God"
  33,18,"God knows the meddlers among you and the ones telling their brethren: \"Come over to our side!\" They only take part in conflict for a little while"
  33,19,"skimping towards you (all). Whenever fear comes over them, you will see them looking at you, their eyes rolling around like someone whom death has almost seized. Once fear leaves them. they will lash out at you (all) with [their] sharp tongues, yet skimping about [doing] any good. Those persons do not believe, so God has foiled their actions. That is so easy for God [to do]"
  33,20,"They reckon the Coalition will not go away. If the Coalition should come [again], they would like to be wandering around far away among the [desert] Arabs, asking for news about you. Yet even if they were among you, they would only fight a little"